                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9315 Manchuria/200: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-27T21:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 27, 1939—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 27—8:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1141. My 915, November 20, 10 a.m. I understand that the Soviet-Japanese Mixed
                    Commission which has been sitting at Chita for the purpose of establishing a
                    definite boundary between Mongolia and Manchuria has reached an agreement on
                    this question and that the commission will move to Harbin on January 7 and
                    proceed to the physical demarcation of the frontier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
